title: Fire Forces Evacuation Of 170 Homes In Japan | 10 News
description: More than 170 people have been forced to evacuate after a massive fire tore through a neighbourhood in south-western Japan.  Residents of the Saganoseki district of Oita city fled to an emergency shelter after the blaze broke out during strong winds around 5:40pm on Tuesday and spread to more than 170 homes. title: Man Charged With Murder Following Double Stabbing At Toddler’s Birthday Party | 10 News
description: A warning for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander viewers: this story contains images of people who have died. title: Gaming Giant Roblox Introduces Age Verification Amid Paedophilia Concerns | 10 News+
description: Roblox, known as one of the world’s largest gaming platforms, will now request users verify their age. The move comes after a negotiation with eSafety Commissioner Julia Inman Grant, who confirmed Roblox was threatened with fines if they failed to comply. title: UK Spy Agency MI5 Issues Warning To British Politicians Over Chinese Spies | 10 News
description: The UK's spy agency MI5 has issued a stark warning to British politicians. Chinese agents are posing as recruiters to target people who work in Parliament in a bid to steal sensitive documents and gain a strategic advantage. The alert says China's spy agency is using headhunters to conduct outreach at scale, including through websites such as LinkedIn.
